body:
So, you're probably going to think this is some formal post where I announce something that means nothing to you until I explain it (see how I didn't say the "Hello" at the beginning), right? Well, not exactly. 

I've been sitting here as a staff member for almost three years, and all you've most likely come to know me as is "Peachy, the Admin." Just the guy who sits up in his little TeamSpeak office, acting like he's doing things for the server? No? How about the guy who seems like he runs the show behind the scenes, but you actually don't know anything about him or what he does? A bit more likely.

Well, let's start simply. My name is Ryan, and I live in the USA. I am currently a sophomore in High School who enjoys playing tennis, researching medicine, and competitive PvP. Okay, basics done. Let's move on to specifics. My job here? Well, my main priority is making you guys mad. Minor things that I do include handling promotions/demotions, executing changes to policies/rules, setting priorities and goals for the server, managing senior staff, listening to Zac in the support room, etc. The list goes on. Anyway, isn't this exactly what I told you I was? One of the guys who runs the show behind the scenes? Well, yeah. Nothing special, most of you could probably do it better than I can. Let's move on though, there will be time to trash talk me later.

Avicus. You've heard that name before, but you're not sure where, right? Well, yeah, probably from some advertisement on TV or something like that. What is Avicus, though? Is it a business run by a corrupt Senior Staff team trying to gain a ton of power on a Minecraft server? Sounds strange, right? Let's try again. Is it a metaphor for how there are lots of greedy and selfish people in the world whom you can't trust, but also how there are people who try their best to do good for the world? A bit farfetched, don't you think? Alright, one more time. Avicus is a community, upheld by unique and welcoming people. Avicus is a place for friendship, safety, and most of all, fun. Avicus is a place where NO ONE is left behind, ostracized, or purely disregarded, and also a place where EVERYONE has a voice and recognition. 

So, why don't we all work in cooperation to fix the problems that are blocking our path to prosperity? Put away the differences, accusations, and arguments in order to put this place back onto its position of glory. 

Now that I've turned off Gandhi mode, I'm sure you either think I'm crazy and should be demoted, or that I should just be demoted. That may be true, but I told you there will be time to trash talk me later, didn't I? Here are my final questions for you, though:
Who are you, and what makes you unique?
What is it about Avicus that makes you stay with it?
What, in your eyes, is the best path for the server at this moment?

THAT IS ALL AM DONE WASTING TIME

This post truly enlightens my Avicus experience. The mere thought of a user being able to exquisitely craft such thought provoking pieces of Avicus literature is beyond my mortal drain of thought. Your allusions to great historical figures who have stood the test of time and proven themselves as true monuments to the human ideology of peace and cooperation is baffling to me, and frankly... Unfathomable. As you stated, prosperity is but a step away, we must take hold and charge forward into the unknown. For this unknown is one that will remain ever-present in this unavoidable future that lies ahead. So I state, we must forge forward through all uncertainties and cast aside our sore eyes, but accustom ourselves to the glorious and masterpiece that is the Avicus eye. Your integration of common Avicus goings truly has raised my level of satisfaction with this piece. The thought that a user of such power could see down to his pupils as peers is revolutionary. I see Avicus has finally sought to appease its Socialist roots. Hence I say, be gone with this democracy, behold the sovereign state that is Socialist Avicus. Welcome my friends, the Russians may have failed, but we will not.
When we look to our Glorious Nation we are only left in a state bewilderment. Unique... What makes Avicus so unique? Its exquisite attention to detail. The unbelievable detail that goes into Avicus truly enlightens the experience of a user. I for one, am really honored of avicus' uniqueness when it comes to its staff. Never have I seen a user named Ryan dedicate so much time towards the Avicus Network. However, I am not Avicus. I am Iron, I am your comrade in action. For this is not a petty democracy with an admin like yourself reigning your iron hand. No. This is communism, the mere thought that all individuals are equal and shall be just in social status. This is the case with Avicus, and hence I am able to state Who I am. I am Iron, unknown on the server till January of last year I was a mere wildflower in the winds of change. The trail of Avicus led me straight along as I stood the tests of time that Avicus was presented. After my encounters with strange phenomenons and occurrences I am who you see today. "Iron." I believe the question you must ask yourself is why do I stay on Avicus. Is it the jaw dropping appeal to aesthetics? Or is it the untouchable desire to quench the thirst of its users. This question Ryan, can only be answered by your heart. Not mine. This server, oh this server.. It does not need guidance, under our socialist rule, Avicus is well on its way to developing into the prosperous nation is has always sought that status of. However, in this time I state. Let our focus not be silly and malicious people. LET IT BE, to invoke the fires stored within all of our hearts. Together only together, can our fires forge the path ahead that Avicus strives for.
